| `history` | `back()` | void | (goes back) |
| `history` | `forward()` | void | (goes forward) |
| `history` | `go(n)` | void | (jumps n steps) |

## 2.7 Real-World Engineering Utility

- **Responsive Web Design** ŌĆö `window.innerWidth` lets JavaScript adapt layouts dynamically to viewport size.
- **Analytics & Logging** ŌĆö `navigator.userAgent` and `screen.width` are used to gather statistics about user devices.
- **Conditional Redirects** ŌĆö `location.replace()` is used in Single Page Applications (SPAs) for seamless URL updates.
- **Back-Button Customization** ŌĆö `history.go(-1)` powers "Return to previous page" buttons across the web.
- **Browser Detection (legacy)** ŌĆö Older websites used `navigator.appName` to serve browser-specific pages.

> [!NOTE]
> **Modern Note:** Most `navigator.appName` checks now return `"Netscape"` for compatibility ŌĆö this is a common KTU viva trick question.

