#### **Solution to Q (a)**

The **`navigator` object** is a child of the `window` object. It exposes information about the **browser application** and the **client's runtime environment**, such as the browser name, version, operating system, language preferences, and online status.

**Key Properties of the `navigator` Object:**

| # | Property | Return Type | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `navigator.appName` | string | Official name of the browser (most modern browsers return `"Netscape"` for compatibility) |
| 2 | `navigator.appVersion` | string | Version of the browser along with platform and OS details |
| 3 | `navigator.userAgent` | string | Full User-Agent header string sent to servers (most comprehensive browser identifier) |
| 4 | `navigator.platform` | string | Operating system platform (e.g., `"Win32"`, `"Linux x86_64"`, `"MacIntel"`) |
| 5 | `navigator.language` | string | Browser's preferred UI language in IETF format (e.g., `"en-US"`, `"ml-IN"`) |
| 6 | `navigator.languages` | array | List of preferred languages in priority order |
| 7 | `navigator.cookieEnabled` | boolean | Whether the browser has cookies enabled |
| 8 | `navigator.onLine` | boolean | Whether the browser is currently connected to the internet |
| 9 | `navigator.product` | string | Engine name (e.g., `"Gecko"`) |
| 10 | `navigator.geolocation` | object | API to request the user's geographic location (with permission) |
| 11 | `navigator.javaEnabled()` | function | Returns `true` if Java is enabled in the browser (legacy) |

**Two Practical Real-World Uses of `navigator`:**

1. **Device-Aware Content Delivery** ŌĆö E-commerce websites like Amazon use `navigator.userAgent` to determine if the visitor is on a mobile device and serve a mobile-optimized page layout accordingly. A typical check: `if (/Mobi|Android/i.test(navigator.userAgent)) { showMobileLayout(); }`.

2. **Localization and Internationalization** ŌĆö `navigator.language` allows websites to automatically display content in the user's preferred language without requiring manual selection. For example, an Indian news portal might auto-redirect `/` to `/ml/` for Malayalam speakers based on `navigator.language === "ml-IN"`.

3. **Offline Detection** ŌĆö Web apps (Gmail, Google Docs) check `navigator.onLine` to show a "You are offline" banner and queue user actions for later sync.

